1. e4 e5 { My choice for the Open Games is the Four Knights Scotch variation. } 
2. Nf3 {[%mdl 32768]} {[%csl Re5]} { Developing the knight with tempi, hitting the e5-pawn, is our best move against the Open Games. } Nf6 { If they go for the Petrov Defence, we shall do our best to transpose to our main repertoire. } 
3. Nc3 {[%cal Yd2d4][%csl Ge4]} { Protecting our e-pawn and preparing 3. d4. } Bb4 { Is another option against which we play: } ( 3...Nc6 { would be a direct transposition to the Scotch Four Knights. } ) 
4. Nxe5 Bxc3 
5. dxc3 Nxe4?! { Black gets back the pawn, but has to face an unpleasant pin. } 
6. Qe2↑ {[%cal Ge2e8][%csl Re8,Ye4]} { With the initiative. } *

