1. e4 e5 { My choice for the Open Games is the Four Knights Scotch variation. } 
2. Nf3 {[%csl Re5]} { Developing the knight with tempi, hitting the e5-pawn, is our best move against the Open Games. } Nf6 { If they go for the Petrov Defence, we shall do our best to transpose to our main repertoire. } 
3. Nc3 {[%cal Yd2d4][%csl Ge4]} { Protecting our e-pawn and preparing 3. d4. } Bc5?! { A weak move, but very popular at lower levels because of the resemblance with the Italian Opening. We can punish it immediately. } 
4. Nxe5! {[%mdl 32768]} { Winning a clean pawn. } O-O ( { Sometimes they will go for an unsound gambit with } 4...Nc6?! 5.Nxc6 dxc6 { and now the solid } 6.h3! { prevents any shenanigans with ...Bg4 or ...Ng4, and will also allow us to play Qf3 in the future. After } 6...Be6 7.d3 { we have a clean extra pawn with meagre compensation. } ) 
5. d4 {[%csl Gd4,Ge4,Yc5]} { And we have a clear advantage, an extra pawn and good development. } *

