4. Bg2 g6 
5. d3 Bg7 
6. Be3 e6 ( { Another interesting alternative for Black is } 6...e5 { grabbing space in the center but loosening the grip on the d5-square. In this case, developing the knight on h3 to reinforce f2-f4 makes a lot of sense. } 7.Nh3!? Nge7 8.O-O O-O 9.f4 exf4 10.Nxf4 { with decent control over d5. The game was played at the rapid time control, mistakes were made by both sides, but I suggest browsing over the moves to see a nice exchange sacrifice followed by a kingside attack. } 10...b5 11.a3 b4 12.axb4 cxb4 13.Ncd5 Bxb2 14.d4! Bxa1 15.Nf6+ Kh8 16.Qxa1 Qa5 17.Qd1 Ng8 18.N4d5 Be6 19.Nxg8 Rxg8 20.Bg5 Rg7 21.Bf6 Rag8 22.Ne3 Qb6 23.Qd2 Na5 24.h4 b3 25.Rb1 b2 26.c4 Rb8 27.Kh2 Qb4 28.Qf2 Nxc4 29.Nxc4 Bxc4 30.d5 Qb6 31.Rxb2 Bb3 32.Qe1 Qb4 33.Qa1 Rbg8 34.Qxa7 Qc4 35.Qxf7 { 1-0 (35) Artemiev,V (2704)-Dubov,D (2696) Sochi RUS 2018. } ) 
7. Qd2 Nge7 
8. Bh6 O-O 
9. h4 { They now have to find a way to deal with the threat h4-h5 followed by hxg6-Bxg7 and Qh6 with a swift mating attack. } Nd4? { Madejska tries to counterattack the c2 square, but this is not good enough. } ( { The best defence is } 9...Bxh6! 10.Qxh6 f6! { with the idea } 11.h5? g5! { followed by ... Kh8 and ...Ng8 trapping the queen. However, unless your opponent specifically knows this idea beforehand, it's highly unlikely that they will spot in the game. Just to be safe, after 10...f6 we shall retreat with the queen to d2 - our model game Adams-Ward [/variation/41248791/#/10/b] deals with this scenario. } ) ( { The following line is an example of what can happen if they don't believe in our attack, } 9...Rb8?! 10.h5! b5 11.Bxg7 Kxg7 12.hxg6 hxg6 13.Qh6+ Kf6 { 13...Kg8 14.Qh8 } 14.e5+! Nxe5 15.Ne4+ Kf5 16.Qg5 { . } ) 
10. O-O-O ( { Even better is } 10.Bxg7 Kxg7 11.h5 Ng8 12.O-O-O { followed by f4 with a very dangerous initiative. } ) f5? { Lashing out when you are already weak on the kingside can hardly be the best idea, and Black is duly punished. } ( { Black could have still tried the defence } 10...Bxh6 11.Qxh6 f6 { . } ) 
11. h5! { Dworakowska already has a winning attack, and it flows quite nicely. } Rf7 
12. Nh3 { Bringing more pieces to the attack. } Bxh6 
13. Qxh6 Rg7 
14. Ng5 fxe4 
15. hxg6! { Opening up the h-file for the rook. } Ndf5 
16. gxh7+ Kh8 { Madejska tries to use the h-pawn as a shield, but it's too late. } 
17. Qf6! Qe8 
18. g4 Qg6? ( { Or } 18...Nd4 19.Ncxe4 { followed by Ng3-h5 is crushing. } ) 
19. Qf8+ { And Madejska resigned as she is mated on the next move. } 1-0

