8. Qe2 Bb7 
9. Bg5! {[%csl Rf6]} { Developing our last minor piece and pinning the knight. } Be7 
10. O-O-O! { By far the most aggressive plan it to castle on the queenside. Our king is safe, our rooks are connected, and we are now prepared for the kingside pawn avalanche attack. } O-O 
11. h4! h6 
12. Ne5 {[%cal Rh6g5,Gh1h8,Gd3h7,Ge2h5][%csl Gg5,Gh1]} { Is a fun line to have on the board. The bishop can't be captured - we will mate on the h-file rapidly - and our attack is looking good. } *

