7. Nb3! fxe5 
8. dxe5 Be7 
9. Nbd4! { Hitting the pawn on e6. }Nxd4? ( 9...Ndb8 { is the only move after which we are obviously much better, but what happens if they trade knights? } ) 
10. Nxd4 {[%csl Re6]} { The e6-pawn hangs. Watch out now for the nice trap! } c6 
11. Nxe6 {[%cal Ye6d8]} Qa5+ 
12. Bd2 Qxb5 
13. Nc7+ {[%cal Gc7b5,Gc7e8][%csl Re8,Rb5]} { Winning the queen. This hasn't been played before at master level according to my database, but it's a trap worth knowing. } *

